title: Major overhaul: toward .NET Core and newer design
Revert "Major overhaul: toward .NET Core and newer design"
Revert "Major overhaul: toward .NET Core and newer design"
Remove `Core` from MSPC Core package namespace.
Peaks with p-value less than TauW are considered weak
Expose sets of classified (stringent/weak) and processed (confirmed/discarded) peaks via public properties.
Polish the Processor class and simplify attributes allowing each processed interval having multiple attributes (aka tags)
Update license header of all the files in the solution.
Remove Stats property of the Sets class.
Pre-processed and processed peaks are all stored as processed peaks
Store all the peaks in a single data structure
Add unit test to assert correctly confirming/discarding peak when samples are Technical or Biological replicates
Unit tests for C and MultipleIntersection
Update CommandLineOptions class leveraging `Microsoft.Extensions.CommandLineUtils` and add required unit tests.
Some CLI code clean-up and extend unit tests.
Increase code coverage for Core prg & implement related bug fixes
Replace the cached data for right-tailed probability of Chi-squared distribution with functions from MathNet library
Do not define a max p-value, and remove related checks
Some code smell fixes and documentation update
Refactor cancel-rerun unit test to avoid race condition.
Implement Concrete MSPC and refactor: MSPC > Mspc
Parser input according to user-defined bed parser configuration
Accept wildcard character for input files
Improve the performance of consensus peaks determination
Write header to consensus peaks file & update unit tests
Update CLI config to accept a percentage of input as the value of C
Fix a bug with reading input samples specified via wildcard chars expanded at shell-level
Fix a bug computing X-sqrd for consensus peaks
Fix bugs computing RTP and Adj p-value
Add help and version options to CLI command parser
Throw a warning if a given tauW is lower than tauS.
Implement a Count function for the Sets type
Change type of C and DF to int
Fix a bug formatting summary statistics
Delete temporary files created by unit tests, once the tests are concluded.
Unions peaks on all chrs before running multiple testing correction
Export data in both standard BED and MSPC format
Build a tree after all intervals are added (at "Initializing" step), not at first time the tree is queried
Add an option to specify the path in which analysis results should be persisted
Make tracking a list of overlapping peaks an optional feature, which is disabled by default
Memory optimization by improving how attributes are stored for a processed peak.
Overhaul data processing: modify input instead of creating a separate set for output
Collapse multiple interval trees into a single tree.
Fix a bug truncating column content
Adds the option of specifying degree of parallelism
Raise an exception when a given parser config file does not exist.
Formatting and colouring error and success messages.
Log input filename differently for Logger and Console
Add `-` and `--` before missing argument names.
Add the option to specify a folder where to read input files
Format appveyor and travis yaml files.
Parser and export double types appreciating culture info
Report CLI table headers in log file
Report elapsed time in the output.
Hint how to use help when an exception occurs.
Change CLI assembly name from CLI to mspc.
Add annotation BED files via LFS.
Update dependencies, & replace OpenCover with .net core coverage.
Remove annotation files stored via LFS
Build travis website when push/pr to master.
Update website's template to Docusaurus v2
Added MSPC validation figure R script and input file
Report `inf` as a result of converting 0 to -Log10 format
Change the target framework from .NET Core 3.x to .NET 5.x.
Set ExitCode according to the termination status
Adjust maximum value of C according to the number of given input samples
Export results to a given output directory and log the absolute path
Report the export path on console
Developed a first version R package for mspc
Update Docusaurus version & add algolia to dependencies
Github actions for running tests on linux
Scripts to benchmark different versions of MSPC
Update CLI to the v2 of System.CommandLine
Set the default max degree of parallelism to the max allowed by the underlying scheduler
Extend tests asserting if peaks on all chrs and strands are exported
Fix a bug reporting incorrect number of consensus peaks on the terminal
Bump minimatch, recursive-readdir and serve-handler in /website
